webpackJsonp([33794019676863],{1021:function(t,e){t.exports={data:{wordpressPost:{title:"The Perfect Ponytail &#8211; Only Way Sexier!",content:'<p>The perfect ponytail is &#8211; well &#8211; perfect and for a variety of reasons.</p>\n<p>Firstly, it can take you anywhere &#8211;<strong> the office, the gym, coffee or the club</strong>. But, and this is a big but, only if it&#8217;s done right. The good news is doing it right is SO much easier than you might think.</p>\n<p>Here&#8217;s a very easy guide by my pal <strong>Aleks Abadia</strong> from <a href="http://esstudio.com.au">Esstudio Galleria</a> &#8211; a very cool little joint in the hipster burb of <strong>Chippendale in Sydney</strong>. By the way &#8211; don&#8217;t let that put you off if hipsters aren&#8217;t your thing. It&#8217;s one of the most welcoming salons you&#8217;ll ever stumble across. Promise. But back to the perfect pony.</p>\n<p>Section hair into two parts, front and back.</p>\n<p>Pull the bottom section into a loose ponytail at the nape of the neck.</p>\n<p><strong>Hold the front section straight up</strong> and gently back comb with a back-combing brush. (Back-combing is simply brushing towards the roots rather than the tradition brushing from roots to ends). Doing so will give you&#8217;re pony volume at the crown which is where you want it.</p>\n<img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-532" src="http://dcqiwphk5imn5.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/13152853/bobby-pins-719091-200x300.jpg" alt="" width="200" height="300" srcset="http://dcqiwphk5imn5.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/13152853/bobby-pins-719091-200x300.jpg 200w, http://dcqiwphk5imn5.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/13152853/bobby-pins-719091-768x1152.jpg 768w, http://dcqiwphk5imn5.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/13152853/bobby-pins-719091-683x1024.jpg 683w" sizes="(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px" /> <img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-547" src="http://dcqiwphk5imn5.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/13154005/bamboo-mini-hairbrush-43238-194x300.jpg" alt="" width="194" height="300" srcset="http://dcqiwphk5imn5.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/13154005/bamboo-mini-hairbrush-43238-194x300.jpg 194w, http://dcqiwphk5imn5.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/13154005/bamboo-mini-hairbrush-43238.jpg 648w" sizes="(max-width: 194px) 100vw, 194px" />\n<p><strong><em>Yes &#8230; this is a Bobbi Pin.<a href="http://www.ladyjayne.com.au"> Lady Jayne </a>do a great range. You&#8217;ll need a few of those. And this little <a href="http://www.thebodyshop.com.au/haircare/brushes">The Body Shop </a>brush is cute yes? Pop it in your handbag in case you need touch ups on the go. </em></strong></p>\n<p>Next, pin the top section on <strong>each side with a Bobbi pin or three</strong>. Use the pins to push the hair up further at the front.</p>\n<p>Next, take the lower section and bring it up to meet the top section. Gather all of the hair into one bunch and tie with an elastic.</p>\n<p>Finally, take a small section of hair from the pony and wrap it <strong>tight around the base to hide the elastic</strong>. Use a Bobbi pin to hold and then, a little hair spray.</p>\n<img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-1707" src="http://dcqiwphk5imn5.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/17144358/ELEVEN-Australia-Give-Me-Hold-Flexible-Hairspray-186x300.jpg" alt="" width="186" height="300" srcset="http://dcqiwphk5imn5.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/17144358/ELEVEN-Australia-Give-Me-Hold-Flexible-Hairspray-186x300.jpg 186w, http://dcqiwphk5imn5.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/17144358/ELEVEN-Australia-Give-Me-Hold-Flexible-Hairspray-768x1240.jpg 768w, http://dcqiwphk5imn5.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/17144358/ELEVEN-Australia-Give-Me-Hold-Flexible-Hairspray-634x1024.jpg 634w" sizes="(max-width: 186px) 100vw, 186px" /><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-1708" src="http://dcqiwphk5imn5.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/17145106/Blush-Style-Collection-Straightener-Pack-S1455PAU--300x121.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="121" srcset="http://dcqiwphk5imn5.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/17145106/Blush-Style-Collection-Straightener-Pack-S1455PAU--300x121.jpg 300w, http://dcqiwphk5imn5.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/17145106/Blush-Style-Collection-Straightener-Pack-S1455PAU--768x309.jpg 768w, http://dcqiwphk5imn5.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/17145106/Blush-Style-Collection-Straightener-Pack-S1455PAU--1024x411.jpg 1024w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" />\n<p><strong><em><a href="http://elevenaustralia.com/hair-products/">Eleven Australia&#8217;s Give Me Hold Flexible Hairspray</a> is perfect &#8211; super hold no weight. And the <a href="http://www.remington-products.com.au/women/hair-care/straighteners.aspx">Remington Blush Style Collection Straightener Pack</a> is also an excellent choice.</em></strong></p>\n<p>The super keen can tong the pony so that it has even more volume and some loose, sexy curls.</p>\n<p>Yes, yes, yes! <strong>You can do it and you will look AMAZING</strong>! Let us know how you go. And if you&#8217;ve any extra tips and tricks, share them with us. We can add your comments in. We&#8217;re all friends here.</p>\n',better_featured_image:{source_url:"http://dcqiwphk5imn5.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/17140252/ELEVEN-Australia-Spring-Racing-2016_1.jpg"},categories:[{slug:"hair",name:"Hair"}]},site:{siteMetadata:{title:"The Beauty Insider"}}},pathContext:{id:"62dbc514-f2e8-5e21-8d19-7cf830f7c52a"}}}});
//# sourceMappingURL=path---ponytail-way-sexier-bc7874ff4a5c4a770d8d.js.map